player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Player and Money","Use this option to donate money to other players or your faction. Commanders may add or remove players from the Server Members List if the feature is enabled"]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Server Members","For MP only. If enabled, this feature will exclude all non-members from using the HQ Ammobox and become Commander. This feature is intended to avoid game ruin by the casual troll in open server environments."]];
//player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Group Selection","For MP only. You can build groups with up to 10 human players. Commander is excluded of this function."]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Base Static Emplacement","Purchased static weapons won't despawn if you leave them in a base or zone, AI garrison will man them. Reinforce places as you desire."]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Fast Travel","When there are no enemies nearby, fast travel to FIA controlled places. Commander also has the ability to use this option on HC groups, selecting the group on HC bar and clicking on this button"]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Ammobox Transfer","When you mount a truck, you may use the Transfer action in the action menu. It will search for nearby ammoboxes and load it's content to the truck's cargo space. You may them unload the truck in your ammobox at HQ for future uses. Before transfering, make sure to unload backpack/vest content into the Truck cargo space and then transfer. TIP: If your HQ Ammobox is full, use this functionality from a nearby truck to add more content to the ammobox as it will then accept everything :)"]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Conquere","Some zones, like Bases or Airports require you use the ""Take the Flag"" action on their respective flags in order to conquer them. Some other, like roadblocks and some outposts, require you defeat the garrison."]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Static Weapons","You may steal static weapons found in enemy bases. Use the proper action to do so. DO NOT unassembled them before using the action!"]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Vehicles","You may buy vehicles for your squad in FIA flags."]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Radio Towers","Destroy or capture Radio Towers in order to break AAF Comms Network. Bases and Airports without Comms cannot perform counter-attacks. Conquering a Radio Tower will give FIA a chance of knowing enemy movements"]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Politics","This is a Civil War. People are not conquered if you cannot conquer their hearts. In game-mechanics this means you cannot conquer cities. The citizens of each town support AAF or FIA in some amount. The dominant faction is the one who owns the city and benefits of their support in Money and Human Resources. Your actions may low AAF Support or raise yours, or both. Killing enemies, accomplishing missions, conquering resources and power-stations affect the amount of citizen support."]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Arsenal","Scavenge for items, weapons and magazines and drop them in your HQ Ammobox. Once you have a specific amount of them, they will be unlocked and added to the Arsenal for personal use. The amount required depends on how many assets FIA has unlocked and number of factories owned. Unlocked weapons, optics and Night-vision Googles may also change AI load-out. Basic Riflemen are specially affected by this: Their load-out will start from small SMGs to having an extra AA / AT launcher. Please note this will not affect their dressing, which will depend on the current FIA Skill Level (helmets and uniform). Arsenal is the standard BIS Arsenal, check their documentation for interaction and use.<br/>To see the required amounts for each group of items to get unlocked, open the HQ Ammobox and you will receive a detailed report."]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Undercover","Click on the button to become Undercover. If you accomplish the requirements, AAF won't attack you sight. On foot, to become Undercover you need to have no weapons or military equipment on sight. You will lose Undercover when you change load-out, get spotted by enemy guard-dogs, plant mines and can be reported by some civilians to AAF. If you are discovered you won't be able to be Undercover on foot again for 30 minutes. In vehicles, to become Undercover you have to get in any civilian vehicle. You will lose Undercover by firing any weapon or being spotted far from a road. If you are discovered you won't be able to be Undercover in that vehicle. Getting close to enemy Bases, Outposts and Roadblocks will also make you lose Undercover."]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Garage","Add any vehicle near your personal Virtual Garage (or factions garage if you are the commander) and keep it safe for future use. Vehicle add option is under the Y menu. Garage management is in HQ options (Flag)."]];
player createDiaryRecord ["Features",["Faction Leader","Same as any Resistance movement, leadership is not as stable as in organised states. Any player can take the role of FIA Force Commander if the actual is not very popular... Upgrade while accomplishing missions and killing enemies and maybe you are the next leader."]];

